_internalIsMobileBrowser

public boolean _internalIsMobileBrowser()
Description copied from interface: WURFLRequest
Says if this request is supposed to come from a mobile browser.
This method is the result of an heuristic for internal use only, and the result is often completely meaningless for the end user.
Consider using Device.getCapability("is_wireless_device") or Device.getVirtualCapability("is_smartphone"), instead, or find here full capabilities documentation.

Specified by:
_internalIsMobileBrowser in interface WURFLRequest
Returns:
true if the request comes from a mobile device
